## 5. Carrier Account Architecture

### The Two Modes

**`lassoed_carrier_account`**
WMS integrated. Full label-print visibility. shipment_ledger
row created at print time. Full reconciliation available.
Invoice matching: tracking_number → shipment_ledger → org_id

**`dark_carrier_account`**
Client entered Cactus credentials into their own platform.
Zero visibility at label print. Invoice-only billing.
Invoice matching: ship_from_address_normalized → locations

### The is_cactus_account Flag
- TRUE (default): Cactus earns margin. Apply markup.
- FALSE: Pass-through. No owned revenue. Skip markup.

### Carrier Account Hierarchy
```
organizations
    └── org_carrier_accounts
            ├── markup_percentage  ← PRIMARY markup
            ├── dispute_threshold
            ├── carrier_account_mode
            ├── is_cactus_account
            └── rate_cards (optional children)
                    ├── service_level
                    └── nickname
```

### All carrier accounts are Cactus/Buku master accounts.
No per-org carrier credentials to store.

