## 6. Rating Engine Architecture

### WMS Integration Flow (lassoed accounts)
```
WMS sends rate request to Cactus API:
  org_id, origin, destination, weight, dimensions
        ↓
Cactus looks up active carrier accounts for this org
        ↓
Cactus calls each carrier API simultaneously:
  FedEx Comprehensive Rates API
  UPS Rating API
  (Phase 2: UniUni, GOFO, ShipX, USPS, etc.)
        ↓
Carriers self-filter by zip coverage
  (no rate returned = not serviceable = excluded)
        ↓
Cactus applies org markup + Single-Ceiling to each rate
        ↓
Cactus logs all rates to rate_shop_log (async)
        ↓
Cactus returns ALL rated options to WMS
        ↓
WMS displays and handles rate selection UI
        ↓
User selects rate → WMS calls Cactus Label Purchase API
        ↓
Cactus purchases label → returns tracking number to WMS
        ↓
WMS prints label
```

### Rate Sorting
```
Default sort: final_merchant_rate ASC (cheapest first)
Optional:     transit_days ASC then final_merchant_rate ASC
Never:        carrier-weighted or manually promoted results
```

Residential and fuel surcharges are already included in
carrier API rate responses. final_merchant_rate accounts
for everything. Cheapest first IS the smartest sort.

### Last-Mile Carrier ZIP Coverage
UniUni, GOFO, and ShipX self-filter by ZIP code.
If a ZIP is not serviceable, no rate is returned.
No ZIP code lookup tables needed in Cactus.
When a carrier expands their network, Cactus automatically
reflects it without any code changes.

### API Error Handling
If a carrier API returns an error (not just no rate):
→ Silently exclude that carrier from results
→ Log error to audit_logs with full context
→ Never fail the entire rate shopping response
→ Return rates from all other carriers normally

### DHL eCommerce — Daily Manifest Requirement
Unlike FedEx and UPS, DHL eCommerce requires a daily manifest
(Driver Summary Manifest) to close out shipments and trigger
pickup. Build a daily manifest job in the DHL eCommerce adapter.
Failure to manifest = packages not collected.

