## 10. Product Architecture

### The Two Portals

**Cactus Portal** — client-facing
Shipments, tracking, meter balance, invoices, AI insights.
Never shows markup, raw costs, or carrier account details.

**The Alamo** — internal Cactus admin only
- Org + carrier account management
- Invoice upload, AI normalization, human review
- Dispute review and resolution
- Rate card management
- Audit logs, meter health

### Phase 1 Build Sequence
```
Stage 1: Schema v1.4.0           ✅ complete
Stage 2: The Alamo shell          ← NEXT
Stage 3: Org + carrier management
Stage 4: Invoice pipeline
Stage 5: Rating engine core
Stage 6: UPS + FedEx integrations
Stage 7: Warehance WMS integration
Stage 8: Cactus Portal
Post:    Phase 2 carriers
```

---

## 11. Coding Philosophy

- WHY comments on every non-obvious block
- Rate card failure never halts label production
- Idempotency keys on all label purchases and meter reloads
- Async Shadow Ledger writes — never block rating response
- Graceful carrier API error handling — never fail entire response
- Performance: Rating < 500ms, Label < 2000ms, Dashboard < 1s

---

## 12. Security Standards
- API keys in `.env` only — never hardcoded
- `.env` in `.gitignore` — never committed
- Payment tokens only — raw card data never in Cactus
- Service role key — backend only, never in browser
- All timestamps: `TIMESTAMPTZ`

